reviews.text: This station is really quiet, there's nothing to do here.. and feels a bit dangerous waiting here alone with just another dodgy looking passenger around.. the refreshments shop here  decorated their surrounding area with mugs on trees, tyres as plant pots, a drumset as flower bays good effort and nicely maintained but it looks a bit odd to me.. the station itself is the historical type that looks like the buildings you'll see in old cowboy films, it's a 1 mile walk to the Crediton High Street from here, this is a dual track station, with a little interactive information screen showing train times (the one where you can press to speak to an advisor), there are no toilets here.
Just going through to Barnstaple. But stop here for their Large Store Sainsbury.
Basic little station but no inside waiting room
